{# runbook-step.md.j2 — renders a single runbook step as a self-contained
   markdown fragment.  Used when posting individual steps to Slack threads
   or when streaming step-by-step guidance to the engineer during triage.

   Expected context variables:
     step       — RunbookStep object
     step_total — total number of steps in the runbook
     runbook    — RunbookMatch object (for header context)
     alert      — normalized Alert struct
     classify   — ClassifiedAlert output #}
### Step {{ step.step_number }} / {{ step_total }} — {{ step.title }}

> **Runbook:** {{ runbook.runbook_title }} | **Alert:** {{ alert.name }} | **Priority:** {{ classify.priority }}

{{ step.description }}

{% if step.commands | length > 0 -%}
**Commands to run:**

```bash
{% for cmd in step.commands -%}
{{ cmd }}
{% endfor %}
```
{%- endif %}

{% if step.links | length > 0 -%}
**Reference links:**
{% for link in step.links -%}
- <{{ link }}>
{% endfor %}
{%- endif %}

{% if step.step_number == step_total -%}
---
_This was the last runbook step.  If the issue is resolved, acknowledge the alert
in {{ alert.source | title }}.  If not resolved, escalate or open a P1 incident._
{%- endif %}
